<headline>Severe Thunderstorm Warning issued July 08 at 6:08PM MDT until July 08 at 6:30PM MDT by NWS GreatFalls</headline>
<description>...A SEVERE THUNDERSTORM WARNING REMAINS IN EFFECT UNTIL 630 PM MDT
FOR SOUTHEASTERN LEWIS AND CLARK COUNTY...
At 608 PM MDT, a severe thunderstorm was located 8 miles south of
Wolf Creek, or 21 miles north of Helena, moving northeast at 30 mph.
HAZARD...60 mph wind gusts and penny size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Expect damage to roofs, siding, and trees.
Locations impacted include...
Wolf Creek.
HAIL THREAT...RADAR INDICATED
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.75 IN
WIND THREAT...RADAR INDICATED
MAX WIND GUST...60 MPH</description>
<instruction>For your protection move to an interior room on the lowest floor of a
building.</instruction>
